We shared a moment with Esben Holmboe Bang, Chef at @maaemo – located in Oslo, Norway – who joined the 2021 MICHELIN Guide Nordic countries with 3 Stars in its new location.
 
Our Inspectors’ points of view: An exceptional dining experience in a dramatic, high-ceilinged dining room, where the open kitchen is theatrically lit and time seems to stand still. The surprise menu features expertly crafted and memorable dishes with sublime tastes and textures. The attentive serving team explain each dish with passion.
 
Find the whole MICHELIN Guide Nordics selection for 2021 here: https://bit.ly/3AcQzTE
.
.

node.text:
We spent an amazing moment with @reneredzepinoma chef at @nomacph – located in Copenhagen, Denmark – freshly promoted from Two to Three MICHELIN Stars in the Nordics Guide 2021. A round of applause for all his team members!

Our Inspectors’ points of view: This elegant yet relaxed waterside restaurant offers a unique experience, from the greenhouses at the entrance to the ingredients on the plate. The test kitchen is one of the most advanced in the world and offers a tasting menu of creative, complex dishes with vivid natural flavors. Professional, informal service puts guests at ease. Book well in advance.

Find the whole MICHELIN Guide Nordics selection for 2021 here: https://bit.ly/3AcQzTE
.
.
.
#MICHELINGuideNORDIC #ThreeMICHELINStar #Restaurant #chef #gastronomy

The 2021 selection of the MICHELIN Guide for the Nordic countries will be revealed next Monday ✨
In the meantime we are looking back at last year’s winners, including Tina Kragh Vildgaard, the laureate of the MICHELIN Welcome & Service Award. 
She helps creating a truly memorable dining experience for her guests working hand-in-hand with husband @evjordnaer, chef at @restaurantjordnaer — 2 Stars in the 2020 selection — in Gentofte, Denmark. 

Who do you think will be going home with an award this year:

Mentor chef award -> ?
Young chef award -> ?
Welcome and Service award -> ?
Sommelier award-> ?

Let us know in the comment section 👇

Check out our stories next Monday to discover the new laureates or join us on
https://youtu.be/BGSJreIiF1c

🎥 @nordic_chefs 
.
.
.
#MICHELINGuideNORDIC #TwoMICHELINStars#Restaurant #WelcomeServiceAward #chef#gastronomy

The MICHELIN Guide makes you discover the diversity of Zagreb's culinary scene and its rich cuisine built around exceptional local products. We stop at @res_tac_ where we meet chef @miletic_v, her gardener and her producers coming from Zagreb County. The men show us their wonderful range of local products (goat cheese, wine and honey) and share their specific attributes with us.
 
On the threshold between East and West, Zagreb and its county offer a rich and stunning gastronomic scene embodied by talented chefs who are devoted to highlighting the quality of the local ingredients. In a residential district outside the city centre, chef Vesna Miletic prepares Mediterranean-influenced dishes composed of fresh product directly coming from the city markets and her local producers. Let's discover a female chef, her producers and their product which make the gastronomic reputation of this stunning capital city!
 
Cosmopolitan buzz of @zagrebtourist and @visitzagrebcounty may strike you.
 
📍 Zagreb, Croatia . .

The MICHELIN Guide takes you to Zagreb to discover the treasures of the capital city of Croatia, their chefs, their products and their producers. We take a closer look at the establishment @esplanadezagreb where Chef @anagrgicchef runs the kitchen of two restaurants Zinfandel's and Le Bistro Esplanade – both distinguished with a Plate in the MICHELIN Guide Croatia 2020.
 
On the threshold between East and West, Zagreb and its county offer a rich and stunning gastronomic scene marrying culinary influences from continental and Mediterranean countries. Among the restaurants of the city, two are housed in Esplanade hotel considered as one of the capital's most popular places for eating. While the French classic Bistro is a smartly dressed yet informal all-day place, the luxurious Zinfandel's restaurant effortlessly combines the elegance of a bygone era with the ambience of a contemporary dining room. Chef Ana Grgić Tomić prepares ambitious menus offering Croatian classics, like strukli, alongside modern European dishes.
 
Cosmopolitan buzz of @zagrebtourist and @visitzagrebcounty may strike you.
 
📍 Zagreb, Croatia

To celebrate International Sustainable Gastronomy Day, chefs and heads  of restaurants awarded a MICHELIN Green Star are sharing some recipes with us that help make the world a little greener!
 
Today, it’s Chef @dominiquecrenn’s turn. At the head of three-MICHELIN-Starred @atelier.crenn in San Francisco, she chips in with this offering that is a  great way to eat up all those perfect summer tomatoes. Today’s recipe is for juicy, simple confit and marinated tomato salad – one of her favorite ways to enjoy this simple pleasure!
 
Yield: 4

Thanks for the recipe, Chef Dominique Crenn! 

Share your version with us 👉Tag @michelinguideand use #MICHELINGUIDEATHOME

To celebrate International Sustainable Gastronomy Day, chefs at the head of restaurants awarded a MICHELIN Green Star are sharing some recipes that help make the world a little greener!
 
To @massimobottura, it’s essential to “never let food go to waste.” The Chef of Three-MICHELIN-Starred Osteria Francescana shares this message of hope and goodwill in the form of his grandmother’s recipe for traditional Passatelli. In this recipe, the star of the show are humble breadcrumbs, which are for him the epitome of the “waste not, want not” food ethic.
 
Thanks for the recipe, Chef Massimo Bottura! 

Illustrations by @alice.vdw

Today we celebrate International Sustainable Gastronomy Day with chefs and foodies around the world. 

We’re kicking it off with this amazing recipe for herb butter artichoke tacos handed to us from Chef Gary Yin, who helms restaurant King’s Joy in Beijing, 3 stars and a MICHELIN Green star in the MICHELIN China Guide 2021. 
 
Celebrate with us by making the recipe at home and share the results in your story tagging @MICHELINGUIDE and @legengaryin!
 
Serves: 4, 3 tacos per pax

Tip from the chef: You can crack fresh black pepper and/or a few drops of Tabasco for more pop!

Thanks for the recipe, Chef Gary Yin! 

Share your version with us 👉Tag @michelinguide and use #MICHELINGUIDEATHOME

Congratulations to @donangienyc and @rezdoranyc! Each restaurant earned a MICHELIN Star! Chefs-owners Angie Rito and Scott Tacinelli of Don Angie and @stefano_secchi of @rezdoranyc chatted with @massimobottura of Three Star Osteria Francescana in Modena, Italy about redefining Italian-American cuisine and their favorite pastas. 

Our Inspectors describe Don Angie as "A modern Italian American menu with a true global flair. Think sourdough pasta and fior di latte mochi for dessert. They handle bold flavors with creativity and finesse." 
They say @rezdoranyc "offers authentic, regionally focused Italian fare. The quality and execution continued to impress time and again

Thanks to chef @massimobottura for this interview!

Thanks to our partner @caviar! #caviar

See the entire MICHELIN Guide New York selection for 2021 at https://bit.ly/3tL6PYT
and stay tuned for more of the 2021 MICHELIN Guide announcements.

We shared a moment with Esben Holmboe Bang, Chef at @maaemo – located in Oslo, Norway – who joined the 2021 MICHELIN Guide Nordic countries with 3 Stars in its new location.
 
Our Inspectors’ points of view: An exceptional dining experience in a dramatic, high-ceilinged dining room, where the open kitchen is theatrically lit and time seems to stand still. The surprise menu features expertly crafted and memorable dishes with sublime tastes and textures. The attentive serving team explain each dish with passion.
 
Find the whole MICHELIN Guide Nordics selection for 2021 here: https://bit.ly/3AcQzTE
.

We spent an amazing moment with @reneredzepinoma chef at @nomacph – located in Copenhagen, Denmark – freshly promoted from Two to Three MICHELIN Stars in the Nordics Guide 2021. A round of applause for all his team members!

Our Inspectors’ points of view: This elegant yet relaxed waterside restaurant offers a unique experience, from the greenhouses at the entrance to the ingredients on the plate. The test kitchen is one of the most advanced in the world and offers a tasting menu of creative, complex dishes with vivid natural flavors. Professional, informal service puts guests at ease. Book well in advance.

Find the whole MICHELIN Guide Nordics selection for 2021 here: https://bit.ly/3AcQzTE
.

node.text:
Today’s recipe is for a simple but dainty food, Carpaccio. While traditionally composed of very fine raw meat, and simply marinated, the carpaccio of the day is a cod fish version which may delight fish lovers.
Stefaan Couttenye, chef at @auberge_t_hommelhof – Bib Gourmand in the MICHELIN Guide Belgium and Luxembourg 2021 – shares with us the secret of preparation of his marinated cod carpaccio.

Measurement equivalents:
400g= 14.1 oz
10cl= 35.2 fl oz
100g= 3.5 oz
 Tip: When making a fish carpaccio, make sure the fish is very fresh, and the skin and bones have been removed.

Thanks for the recipe, Chef Stefaan Couttenye!

Illustrations by @alice.vdw 
Share your version with us 👉Tag @michelinguide and use #MICHELINGUIDEATHOME

node.text:
Coming from a family which has always supported sustainable food production, the Chef @caterinaceraudo prepares dishes that reflect the beauty and biodiversity of the Italian region of Calabria at the Green MICHELIN Starred @ristorantedattilo. Although this agriturismo nestled in the countryside made its name through its organic wine and olive oil for the past few years, it has also been turning its attention to a gastronomic offer serving top quality, modern and creative cuisine.
 
The friendly and hospitable Ceraudo family live in an eco-sustainable way, harvesting most of the ingredients used in Dattilo. The need for raw materials is largely met by self-production, starting with olives and oil, but also vines and wine, oranges and vegetable gardens, letting the seasons ensure biodiversity to offer the best ingredients. The Ceraudos buy very few products from outside and use every part of them for the restaurant or to feed animals in order to limit waste as much as possible. A further step in this sustainable direction to become energy independent at Dattilo was to equip themselves with photovoltaic panels.
 
"Man is a damage to the earth, but at the same time he is its savior ; with alternative methods of cultivation he will be able to do better and better and recreate what he has destroyed." 
 
Swipe right to check out the chef’s culinary commitments!

📍 Strongoli, Italy 

Illustration by @alice.vdw

The highlight of the MICHELIN Guide Croatia 2021 is that three restaurants have been awarded 1 Star. The country offers chefs high quality local products that inspire them to go above and beyond every day to delight their customers. Congratulations to all their team!
 
Located in the south of Losinj Island, Alfred Keller is making its mark in the @boutiquehotelalhambra. Supervised by @christiankuchler85, the culinary offerings change daily and highlight the best of Croatian products in a French style.

The Italian chef, Emanuele Scarello, came to Croatia this summer to work on a new gastronomic destination: Agli Amici Rovinj. Attached to a luxury hotel, he takes on the codes from the Italian restaurant @agliamici1887, while paying specific attention to products from the Mediterranean and the Istrian region.
 
Located in the modern Hilton Costabella hotel in Rijeka, @nebo.restaurant.lounge with its cocktail bar overlooks the coast of Kvarner. Explore the precise and authentic cuisine of the young chef Deni Sdroc, already well-known in the region.

📍 Croatia

Today’s recipe is for a Korean style vegetable pot-au-feu made by using seasonal summer vegetables. All the trim and peel of vegetables are used to make a stock, which gives us a zero waste recipe.
Son Jong-won, chef at @lamant_secret – awarded 1 Star in the MICHELIN Guide Seoul 2021 – shares the secrets of preparation of his pot-au-feu version.
 
Lists of the ingredients:

For the vegetable trim anchovy stock:
3L, water
15g, anchovy
15g, kombu
5ea, large scallion root
50g, white radish peel
50g, carrot peel
50g, pumpkin peel
50g, purple cabbage trim
 
For the vegetable Mille Feuille:
1ea, napa cabbage
2ea, carrot
1ea, purple cabbage
20ea, sesame leaf
10ea, swiss chard
1/2ea, white radish
1/2ea, pumpkin
2ea, yellow zucchini

To assemble the pot-au-feu:
Vegetable trim anchovy stock
Vegetable mille feuille
2ea, bok choy
1ea, lemon
Salt and pepper
Summer flowers (zucchini, chives, scallion)

Tip of the chef : Dried anchovy can be removed and double amount of kombu can be added for a vegetarian version of the recipe.
Thanks for the recipe, Chef @jw.sson! 
 Share your version with us 👉Tag @michelinguide and use #MICHELINGUIDEATHOME
